# Peer Care Connect Project Context

## Project Overview
Peer Care Connect is a comprehensive platform connecting musculoskeletal health practitioners (osteopaths, sports therapists, massage therapists) with clients. The platform facilitates booking, session management, treatment notes, and practice analytics.

## Current Architecture
- **Frontend**: React + TypeScript + Vite
- **Backend**: Supabase (PostgreSQL + Edge Functions)
- **Authentication**: Supabase Auth
- **Payments**: Stripe integration
- **Real-time**: Supabase Realtime subscriptions
- **Deployment**: Vercel (frontend), Supabase (backend)

## Key Features Implemented
- Multi-role authentication (client, practitioner roles)
- Marketplace for practitioner discovery
- Booking system with calendar integration
- Real-time session management
- Treatment notes (SOAP, DAP, Free Text formats)
- Client progress tracking
- Practice analytics dashboard
- Stripe payment processing
- File upload for qualifications
- Real-time notifications

## Database Schema
- `users` - User profiles and practitioner data
- `client_sessions` - Booking and session management
- `treatment_notes` - Clinical documentation
- `progress_metrics` - Client progress tracking
- `progress_goals` - Treatment goals
- `session_feedback` - Post-session feedback
- `subscriptions` - User subscription management

